         <abstract>
            <p>Exponential windowing is a widely used technique for suppressing the effects of old data as new data is added to a matrix. Specifically, given an n × p matrix X&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; and a "forgetting factor" β ∈ (0, 1), one works with the matrix &lt;tex-math&gt;$\operatorname{diag}(\beta^{n - 1}, \beta^{n - 2}, \ldots, 1)X_n$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. In this paper we examine an updating algorithm for computing the QR factorization of &lt;tex-math&gt;$\operatorname{diag}(\beta^{n - 1}, \beta^{n - 2}, \ldots, 1)X_n$&lt;/tex-math&gt; and show that it is unconditionally stable in the presence of rounding errors.</p>
          </abstract>
